{#
    Recently Viewed
    ================
    Theme Settings → "تفعيل قسم شاهدته مؤخراً" (`recently_viewed_enabled`).
    Salla keeps no "recently viewed" history of its own, so this is tracked
    entirely client-side (`js/modules/recently-viewed.js`, `localStorage`) —
    hidden by default and only revealed once there's at least one other
    product in the visitor's history, so it never shows an empty shelf.

    Include with `exclude_id: product.id` on the single product page so a
    product never lists itself; omit it elsewhere (cart, home).

        {% include 'partials.utility.recently-viewed' with { exclude_id: product.id } %}
#}
<section class="section recently-viewed" data-recently-viewed data-exclude-id="{{ exclude_id|default('') }}" hidden>
    <div class="container">
        <div class="section__head">
            <div class="section__heading">
                <h2 class="section__title">{{ trans('product.recently_viewed_title') }}</h2>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="recently-viewed__grid" data-recently-viewed-list></div>
    </div>
</section>
